      "snippet": "The 2025 NBA trade deadline came to a close on Feb. 6, at 3 p.m. ET. While this year swapped All-Stars around, how often are All-Stars actually traded? Let's take a look at the most recent examples of All-Stars who went on to play for a different team after the All-Star break (courtesy of Elias Sports Bureau). Anthony Davis , Lakers → Mavericks and Luka Doncic , Mavericks → Lakers (2024-25) In what was considered one of the most shocking trades in NBA history, the Los Angeles Lakers acquired Luka Doncic after shipping Anthony Davis to the Dallas Mavericks , in an effort to solidify their franchise's future in the eventual post- LeBron James era. On Feb. 3, 2025, the Lakers traded Davis, Max Christie and their 2029 first-round pick to the Mavericks in exchange for Doncic, Maxi Kleber and Markieff Morris . Meanwhile, thd two second-round picks. The addition of Davis bolsters the Mavericks' defense as they look for an NBA title in 2025. Doncic will attempt to make back-to-back appearances",
